---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import ProjectPageShell from "../components/ProjectPageShell.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
    title="Grid - Altralight"
    description="Grid is our engine lab: a customized Godot-based core for better workflows, cleaner tooling, and practical experimentation."
    bodyClass="project-page"
>
    <ProjectPageShell
        themeClass="project-theme-grid"
        eyebrow="Engine Lab"
        title="Grid"
        intro="A customized engine core for trying ideas before they get flattened by default workflow assumptions. Built on top of Godot because we value momentum."
        status="Heavy tooling work, workflow cleanup, and general engine tampering. Exactly the kind of trouble it was made for."
        sideNote="Grid exists so the rest of the studio can stop negotiating with default editor behavior every time an idea gets weird."
        stats={[
            { value: "Godot", label: "Base layer" },
            { value: "Tooling", label: "Main target" },
            { value: "WIP", label: "Still mutating" },
        ]}
        panels={[
            {
                kicker: "Why It Exists",
                title: "A custom engine path for our workflow.",
                body: [
                    "Grid Core is where we shape editor, tooling, and workflow around how we actually build things.",
                    "The point is not to replace Godot out of ego. The point is to take a good foundation and push it toward the kinds of projects we actually want to build."
                ]
            },
            {
                kicker: "Foundation",
                title: "Built with respect for what already works.",
                body: [
                    "If you care about what Godot has done for game development, same here. Grid only exists because that engine is worth extending in the first place.",
                    "This is not a from-scratch origin story. It is a practical fork in the road: keep the good parts, fix rough edges, and test ideas faster."
                ]
            },
            {
                kicker: "Mission",
                title: "Practical enough to use. Weird enough to matter.",
                body: [
                    "Grid is part playground and part studio tool for times when a project needs a different answer than the standard pipeline.",
                    "Use it, study it, fork it, ignore it, steal good ideas from it. If it helps another developer make something better, good."
                ]
            }
        ]}
        links={[
            { href: "https://github.com/FadeCrew/Grid", label: "View on GitHub" },
            { href: "/", label: "Back to Homepage", variant: "secondary" },
        ]}
    />
</BaseLayout>
